quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  19,77,"Did you, then, see him who rejected Our verses and said, "I shall certainly be given wealth and children?""
  19,78,"Has he peeped in the unseen or taken a covenant with the Rahman (All-Merciful)?"
  19,79,"Never. We will write what he says and extend for him the punishment extensively."
  19,80,"And We will inherit from him what he is talking about and he will come to Us all alone."
  19,81,"And they have taken gods other than Allah so that they might be a might for them."
  19,82,"Never. They will soon deny their worshipping and they will be just the opposite for them."
  19,83,"Did you not see that We have sent the devils onto the disbelievers inciting them with all their incitements."
  19,84,"So do not huffy about them; We are but counting for them a countdown."
  19,85,"The day We ill assemble the God-fearing before the Rahman (All-Merciful) as guests"
  19,86,"and will drive the sinners towards the Jahannam as herds towards water,"
  19,87,"they will have no power of intercession except the one who has taken a covenant with the Rahman (All-Merciful)."
  19,88,"And they say, 'The Rahman (All-Merciful) has taken to Himself a son.""
  19,89,"You have come up, indeed, with something so abominable"
  19,90,"that the heavens are about to explode therewith and the earth to burst and the mountains to fall down crumbling,"
  19,91,"for they have ascribed a son to the Raman (All-Merciful),"
  19,92,"while it is not befitting for the Rahman (All-Merciful) to have a son."
  19,93,"There is none in the heavens and the earth, but bound to come to the Rahman (All-Merciful) as a salve."
  19,94,"He has fully encompassed them and precisely calculated their numbers,"
  19,95,"and each one of them is bound to come to Him on the Day of Judgment, all alone."